<div class="modal fade" id="dashboardHelp" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="dashboardHelpLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="dashboardHelpLabel">Dashboard Help</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Purpose</h6>
                    <p>The dashboard provides a quick operational overview (API health, warehouse KPIs, expiring lots, and recent logs).</p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Key Areas</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><strong>API Status:</strong> health check result and a shortcut to Settings.</li>
                        <li><strong>Active Warehouses:</strong> KPI for operational warehouses.</li>
                        <li><strong>Expiring Lots:</strong> count within the configured expiration window.</li>
                        <li><strong>Inbound KPIs:</strong> arrivals, dock assignment, receipt completion, and putaway completion in a selectable window.</li>
                        <li><strong>Outbound KPIs:</strong> picking, checks, and shipments completed in a selectable window.</li>
                        <li><strong>Quick Links:</strong> shortcuts to core modules.</li>
                        <li><strong>Recent Requests / Errors:</strong> latest log entries for fast triage.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Related Screens</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Use <strong>View lots</strong> to open the Lots list filtered by expiration window.</li>
                        <li>Use the <strong>Inbound KPIs</strong> window selector to compare recent inbound throughput.</li>
                        <li>Use the <strong>Outbound KPIs</strong> window selector to compare recent outbound throughput.</li>
                        <li>Open <strong>Logs</strong> to review full Request/Error/Transaction history.</li>
                        <li>Use Quick Links to jump into CRUD modules (Warehouses, Products, Locations).</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h6>Common Issues</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><strong>API status down:</strong> check API runtime and Settings configuration.</li>
                        <li><strong>No log entries:</strong> ensure logging is enabled and traffic exists.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-light border" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
